query_content_es:
Han pasado cuatro días, con dos apareciendo el primer día y uno cada día después.
El primer día, estaban ubicados junto al ombligo y en el escroto;
El segundo día, estaba en la raíz del muslo;
El tercer día, estaba en el pecho;
Hoy, está en el antebrazo.
No hubo anomalías antes de que aparecieran. Después de despertarme por la mañana, sentí un poco de dolor en un área determinada, y había una pequeña pústula allí. No pica, pero duele un poco.
La forma específica se muestra en la imagen. Uno ha sido exprimido y probablemente no se trató correctamente, por lo que se infectó nuevamente, y uno no ha sido exprimido.
Otra información: El lugar donde vivo es oscuro y húmedo, con muchos mosquitos; ¡No he tenido relaciones sexuales recientemente!
Por favor, dame algunos consejos de tratamiento. Si aparece otro mañana, voy a desmoronarme...

query_content_en:
It's been four days, with two appearing on the first day and one each day thereafter. 
On the first day, they were located next to the navel and on the scrotum;
On the second day, it was at the root of the thigh;
On the third day, it was at the chest;
Today, it is on the forearm.
There were no abnormalities before they appeared. After waking up in the morning, I felt a bit of pain in a certain area, and there was a small pustule there. It's not itchy, but a bit painful.
The specific shape is shown in the picture. One has been squeezed and probably not treated properly, so it got infected again, and one has not been squeezed.
Other information: The place where I live is dark and damp, with many mosquitoes; I have not had sexual intercourse recently!
Please give me some treatment advice. If another one appears tomorrow, I'm going to break down...

About a month ago. There grew a number of small blisters on the outer side of the right palm. They are translucent. I thought it is eczema. However, I also have beriberi, and it relapses every summer. I soak my foot in Gloss Foot Potion (A traditional Chinese medicines containing Talc powder, salicylic acid, and benzoic acid), enough for a year. I also have Terafen hydrochloride cream, for my beriberi. I applied it onto my palm for a week and it showed no improvement.
Symptom:  Skin is hardening and dry, turning rough.  Have small blisters, not itchy.  Not sure if it is eczema or ring worm.  What kind of medication can heal better?  Please help.
Remark:  You can exclude the problem is caused by the use of mouse pointer.  I am left handed;
